#
# Song of the BoS guard in the pit
#
{630}{}{A hellish creature forged of steel,
An evil mechanical dragon}
{631}{}{Fell upon a peaceful village and wreaks havoc there!}
{632}{}{It burns the people with fire from the sky,
Spits out iron and lead}
{633}{}{And fills the air with its roar, destroying all around...}
{634}{}{But Marcus,
The glorious warrior of light,
Defender of the scorched lands,}
{635}{}{He will put an end to this evil, and save the people from death.}
{636}{}{And wrath burns in his clear gaze,
His eyes are full of resolve,
And upon his splendid crest, three beveled gears.}
{637}{}{The glorious banners were raised,
The ringing horns sang out}
{638}{}{And a minstrel sang words of praise for the lord
A servant brings him his spear and hands him a heavy shield
Marcus speaks a prayer, may the heavens protect him.}
{639}{}{He rode forth boldly on his steed,
Like a whirlwind across the scorched earth
And like a star in the dark blazed the tesla coil upon his spear.}
{640}{}{His words rang out like thunder:
"Wretch, come out and fight! I am a paladin of the Brotherhood of Steel, and I will be the end of you!"}
{641}{}{They clashed in a savage battle,
The sky and the earth boiled,
A fiery onslaught swept all things from the line of fire.}
{642}{}{His shield was melted by the dragon's fire,
And his glorious steed perished in battle
And armor-piercing rounds bit into the sturdy armor.}
{643}{}{The dragon openly mocked him,
Tried to knock the hero off his feet,
But Marcus reached it and hurled his spear into its iron flank.}
{644}{}{And the beast roared, pierced by the spear, and began to spark and moan
Struck by an electric discharge, it started to lose altitude!}
{645}{}{The hero, knowing no mercy,
Watched through the fire and smoke
As the rotor-winged creature crashed to the ground before him}
{646}{}{He celebrated victory too soon, the cunning enemy still breathed
And sent a rocket flying toward Marcus...}
{647}{}{[Booooooom! Badaboom!]}
{648}{}{Blood streamed like a river down his armor,
He cast away his shattered helmet}
{649}{}{The combat capability of all systems had already dropped to the minimum}
{650}{}{His armor was almost destroyed,
The reactor began to leak,
But the paladin drew from its sheath a heavy entropic sword.}
{651}{}{The induction accumulator awakened the weapon of light,
And the sword, roaring like a fighter jet, gathered boundless power.}
{652}{}{The hero burned through the enemy like butter, with a single sweep of his hand
The serpent fell apart hideously into hideous pieces.}
{653}{}{Gaping holes were torn in the warrior's chest
He was all torn and burned,
He had lost all his strength in battle and was gravely wounded,}
{654}{}{Rounds had ripped through his armor, filled with depleted uranium,
And when they lifted Marcus up, he had three dozen wounds...}
{655}{}{O knight Marcus the Unyielding,
Mourned by a hundred young maidens}
{656}{}{Lies buried beneath the tree
With bright prayers sung over him}
{657}{}{And to that tree, above the grave, his travelling shield is nailed
And his spirit, with the same strength, still guards these lands from foes!}
{658}{}{La-la-la-la la-la-lay la-la-li-la-ley!
La-la-la-la la-la-lay la-la-li-la-la!}
{659}{}{La-la-la-la la-la-lay la-la-li-la-ley!
La-la-la-la la-la-lay la-la-li-la-la!}

