{3138}{}{Economic miracle. High-profit business. Chip's new canning factory. Canned goods, stew, liver. Those wishing to earn - please come to the back yard (to the basement, unarmed). Mutants - special offer.}
# ** УСЛУГИ ** 3139..3146
{3139}{}{Sessions communing with the spirits of ancestors. Ask Sulik.
Communing with spirits, but cheaper than Sulik. Hakunin.}
{3140}{}{Gauss-therapy sessions at home. Your ammo, my gauss. Ask Cassidy.}
{3141}{}{A thrilling sea cruise with a spectacular night show! "Poseidon-Travel" LLC}
{3142}{}{MAGE SERVICES: I remove curses, break, smash, steal, hack. Inquire at the Slavers Guild. Anyone from the guild.}
{3143}{}{Inviting tough badasses on a tour of the Wasteland with complimentary treatment for inflated self-esteem. The toughest badass.}
{3144}{}{I'll cleanse your town of all living things. *Chosen One*}
{3145}{}{I herd brahmin, have a dog, experienced. Chosen One}
{3146}{}{I'll build from junk, pocket lint, lighters, flowers, syringes, necklaces - vacuum cleaners, tractors, excavators, jet planes, perpetual motion machines of the first and second kind. Contact Wretch, NCR.}
# ** АКЦИИ ** 3147..3154
{3147}{}{We accept slavers wholesale and retail for a good reward. Heads alone are acceptable. NCR Rangers.}
{3148}{}{*In large letters* Hurry! Hurry! Only here and only for you! The "Rusted Enclave Trooper" attraction! You're allowed to knock him on the forehead and kick him in the rear! Somewhere in the desert, you'll find it yourself... Chosen One.}
{3149}{}{"Enclave" LLC holds an open house day! On the program: a merry run across the oil rig, arm-wrestling with Frankie, squats in power armor, plus the "See the bomb and die" excursion! At the end of the program, merry soldiers will escort you to the exit with kicks, shouting "Evacuation!!!" "Enclave" LLC
P.S. Chosen Ones are asked not to bother.}
{3150}{}{We invite you to the new theatrical production "Aliens-7"! Inquire in Redding, at the wanamingo mine!}
{3151}{}{Collect 10 heads of the dead and get a 50% discount on Vault City citizenship! Lynette.}
{3152}{}{You have no money, but have unloved relatives??? We'll help you!!! For a very good fee, you can leave your relatives with us for permanent residence!!! Inquire in the Den, East side, at the Slavers Guild. Metzger.}
{3153}{}{Those wishing to star as victims in the film "Aliens" are asked to visit the wanamingo mine more often.}
{3154}{}{To all the boys from Vault City security!!! Paintball and free beer! Gathering behind the fence, you know where. Citizen-Sergeant STARK}
# ** РАЗНОЕ ** 3155..3175
{3155}{}{Trade: a spear with a sharpened tip (in decent condition) for a Gauss rifle with detailed operating instructions, warranty card and other documentation, if any exists. NO SURCHARGE. Chosen One.}
{3156}{}{Trade twenty golden Gecko pelts for a sawed-off shotgun. Chosen.}
{3157}{}{Trade a turbo plasma rifle with automatic fire capability for an Antioch grenade. Well Chosen One, now we'll see which of us is the real munchkin! Frankie.}
{3158}{}{Trade vertibird key blueprints for the blueprints of the vertibird itself. (Inquire at the Brotherhood of Steel bunker in San Francisco)}
{3159}{}{Will meet a girl, non-smoking, non-drinking, disciplined, who owns a gasoline car, for mutual benefit. Captain of the Tanker "Poseidon Oil" Valdez.}
{3160}{}{Wanted! Name: Randal. Nickname: Tin Woodman. Place of service: Enclave. Lost on a mission to eliminate the Chosen One. Signed: Sergeant.}
{3161}{}{Lots of difficult, dirty and poorly paid work, contact the sheriff of Redding.}
{3162}{}{Give me money, or I'll jump right now! Kitty.}
{3163}{}{The bureaucrats of Vault City are - #%!$ $&*$^!& (Signature illegible)}
{3164}{}{We format the Emperor. Li Shi - free of charge! Everyone else - for $1.95}
{3165}{}{Announcement. The "Dancing Mutant" bar has opened. On the program: a striptease performed by the star of the wastelands, the mutant girl Isolde (stage name). Live music (Rock band "Geiger", vocalist - Harold).}
{3166}{}{Congratulations to all Enclave troopers and Frank on Defender of the Fatherland Day. President.}
{3167}{}{Charming, 34 years old, seeking a man for spending time together. Intimacy welcome (but in secret from my husband). Mrs. Bishop.}
{3168}{}{Will meet a decent man, well-off with a sense of humor. Chosen Ones are asked not to bother. Lynette}
{3169}{}{On July 27, 2247, the Chosen One left Arroyo in search of the GECK and never returned. Not answering on EMS. Whoever finds him is asked to contact the "Poseidon" rig, third level, first cell, and also to remind the Chosen One that he has one month of munchkinism left until game over. Elder, June 27, 2260.}
{3170}{}{Noobs must suffer! Punks}
{3171}{}{Punks must suffer! Noobs}
{3172}{}{You REALLY don't understand anything about the Essence of the Wasteland. Hubologists}
{3173}{}{!!!ATOM SPARKS ALMIGHTILY!!!!}
{3174}{}{Selling 50 Tommy guns or trading them for 50 rounds of .223 pistol ammo. Unknown.}
{3175}{}{OK. Krizalis}

#
# ncr Spy mission quest. Using in q_spy_mission.fos
#

{3180}{}{McClure? You managed to be late again today.}
{3181}{}{I apologize, First Citizen, too much to do. It won't happen again.}
{3182}{}{You always say that. I'd have gotten rid of you long ago, but, alas, that's impossible right now.}
{3183}{}{I don't understand what you mean, First Citizen.}
{3184}{}{McClure, let's drop the hypocrisy when we're alone. We both understand perfectly well what we're talking about.}
{3185}{}{Fine, Lynette. I'm merely obligated to do my duty. I hope the state of affairs will change in the near future.}
{3186}{}{And I hope the status quo will be preserved. Your overconfidence will fail you, and you'll make a mistake. And I'll use it.}
{3187}{}{I'd like to believe you won't get such a chance. Let's set aside our verbal battles and get back to work.}
{3188}{}{I'm listening, advisor.}
{3189}{}{The mood in the City hasn't changed. No significant incidents or crimes have been recorded over the past week.}
{3190}{}{Why, the very fact of your existence, advisor, is a crime!}
{3191}{}{First Citizen, should I leave?}
{3192}{}{Alright, let's forget it, I mustn't give in to emotions. Continue.}
{3193}{}{Several cases of attacks on law enforcement have been recorded in Redding. Discontent among the native residents is growing.}
{3194}{}{Output?}
{3195}{}{Gold mining rates have fallen over the past week. We need more miners. Perhaps we should send some of the servants to the Redding mines.}
{3196}{}{Nonsense. Reinforce the regulator units. So that no one can shirk work. What about NCR?}
{3197}{}{Martial law is still in effect. There were several raider attacks on the Republic's capital, repelled by the NCR army.}
{3198}{}{Have relations between the army and the Brotherhood of Steel remained unchanged?}
{3199}{}{According to reliable sources, Sheyman is trying to establish contact with the paladins. But so far without result.}
{3200}{}{Anything else?}
{3201}{}{No, that's all for today.}
{3202}{}{Disgusting. Though, what else could I expect from a traitor?}
{3203}{}{I suggest we do without labeling. And generally refrain from acts one might regret in the future...}
{3204}{}{Is that a threat, McClure? Don't make me laugh. You're dismissed.}
{3205}{}{Good day, First Citizen.}

#
#Радиопереговоры после выполнения квеста "На связи". redding_common.fos
#
{3300}{}{Doc Johnson here. Calling my people...}
{3301}{}{Birds of a feather. Hello, Painless, long time no see.}
{3302}{}{Is that you, Troy, you underground enema? Sitting there in your vault like some Tom Cruise.}
{3303}{}{Who are you calling an enema. I, for your information, invented anti-jet, while all you can do is treat your miners' anthracosis.}
{3304}{}{Oh, look at him, he invented it. But couldn't set up production, so I had to deal with it...}
{3305}{}{Here we go... When these two get together...}
{3306}{}{Ah, hello Holiday. How are you yourself?}
{3307}{}{Just creaking along. Treating mutants and ghouls a bit. I don't hear Anniversary. Is he here? Holiday calling Anniversary!}
{3308}{}{Yes, I'm here, I'm here. Hello everyone.}
{3309}{}{And good health to you. Fellas, remember how our Anniversary, back in his residency, was looking for a guy's appendix on the left side? Stuck his arm in almost to the elbow and couldn't find it...}
{3310}{}{Alright, alright. It was just once. And besides, I was drunk then. Doesn't count.}
{3311}{}{Oh sure, doesn't count. You found yourself a better spot than any of us, sitting there in NCR, savoring the delights of democracy...}
{3312}{}{You should have such delights! There was an incident, a long time ago though, the Chosen One nearly turned me inside out, said I stole some miner's map of Vault 13. Barely talked my way out. Still shudder when I remember.}
{3313}{}{Serves you right, you bourgeois. Heh-heh...}
{3314}{}{Alright, alright. Listen, Johnson, rumor has it you had a syphilis epidemic over there? How did you sort it out?}
{3315}{}{Had to bust my ass quite a bit. None of them paid attention to the early symptoms, and by the time they did, there were infected up the wazoo. So I went around everywhere like a fool, conducting surveys, figuring out who stuck it in whom, got sick of it. In the end I made a summary table and tracked down the source. Bah on you. You reminded me.}
{3316}{}{Come on, you managed it. Good job.}
{3317}{}{I'll second that. Good job, Johnson.}
{3318}{}{Ooo! Doctor Fung, my respects!}
{3319}{}{Greetings, teacher!}
{3320}{}{Glad to hear you.}
{3321}{}{Hello, boys. I'm also glad to hear all of you. Also glad that we now always have the chance to talk and ask each other for advice. You've all become decent specialists.}
{3322}{}{Thank you, teacher...}
{3323}{}{Don't interrupt your elders! I'm not finished. I believe you should all think about taking on students. Knowledge must not be lost. Well, Troy has already seen to that, I'm aware. But the rest of you - tsk tsk.}
{3324}{}{Alright, teacher.}
{3325}{}{Definitely.}
{3326}{}{Hmm. It hadn't even crossed my mind...}
{3327}{}{Now, boys, I apologize and must leave you. They've just brought me a Chinese man bitten by sharks, I need to attend to him urgently. We'll be in touch next week, I have things to discuss with you.}
{3328}{}{Yes, teacher.}
{3329}{}{Talk later.}
{3330}{}{Good health to you.}
{3331}{}{Hm. Well then. Fellas, you know what? I propose we all have a drink immediately! How do you feel about that?}
{3332}{}{What a question.}
{3333}{}{I support it.}
{3334}{}{So. I've got nothing but spirits, let me run to the bar. Just wait 20 minutes, be human about it.}
{3335}{}{Yeah, alright, alright. Let's all get back on the air in half an hour. And no excuses this time. By the way, just in case - the backup frequency, uh...}
{3336}{}{Use the year penicillin was invented.}
{3337}{}{Works for me.}
{3338}{}{That's it, talk later, fellas, I'm off.}
{3339}{}{Uh-huh.}
{3340}{}{Right.}
###Если в разговор пытается влезть игрок
