# purgatory.fos

{7120}{}{Attention! Recruitment is open for the Trial in Purgatory. To sign up, find the Executor at the entrance of any city in the Wasteland.}
{7121}{}{A powerful electric discharge from your PipBoy sends you to heaven. Though it felt like the blow landed on your neck, from somewhere behind.}
{7122}{}{The belongings you had on you at the moment of death can be reclaimed at the hubologists' bank at any time convenient to you.}
{7123}{}{You have taken part in the hubologists' Trial.
Your team must wipe out the members of the other teams.
After that you can collect your well-earned reward and leave the territory of Purgatory.
For each enemy killed you receive a bonus to your replication account: 300 coins.
For each ally killed a penalty is imposed: 1000 coins. The penalty amount will be deducted from the replication account.}
{7124}{}{In Purgatory the hubologists stage gladiatorial fights between the replicated.}
{7125}{}{|@arg teamColor@ Team @arg team@ |@arg baseColor@: Joining the battle is |@arg teamColor@ @arg name@. }
{7126}{}{Battle participant |@arg team2Color@ @arg killer@ |@arg baseColor@ kills |@arg team1Color@ @arg dead@ |@arg baseColor@ !!}
{7127}{}{No one has signed up yet...}
{7128}{}{The Trial is over. All spectators and participants leave Purgatory.}
{7129}{}{You killed a member of your own team. A penalty of 1000 coins has been deducted from your replication account.}
{7130}{}{You killed a member of the enemy team. 300 coins have been credited to your replication account. Experience gained @arg xp@.}
{7131}{}{The Trial is complete! The team of replication station @arg team@ has won!}
{7132}{}{Attention! The Trial has begun! The box doors are unsealed. Good luck to all battle participants!}


# Реплики для нпц, защищающих свой город. npc_revenge.fos
# предположительно райты
{7200}{}{Citizens of the city! Everyone come here! We must put an end to these killings!}
{7200}{}{Everyone here! I'm going to speak!}
{7200}{}{Enough! We must all stand together against this scum. Come, we'll figure out what to do!}
{7201}{}{Damn, what bad timing...}
{7201}{}{As you say.}
{7201}{}{I'm sick to death of this, damn it.}
{7201}{}{Coming, coming.}
{7201}{}{Yeah, they've gone completely out of control!}
{7202}{}{You can all see for yourselves. There's no need for me to tell you what's happening here. Our problem is the punks.}
{7203}{}{They're killing us, our children, our friends. They're destroying our city. Those scum in blue tights, they want to wipe us off the face of the earth!}
{7204}{}{We survived the war, the radiation, the sandstorms, and even the tyranny of the Chosen One! We must deal with this new threat ourselves.}
{7205}{}{Not a single punk should go unpunished! They're all the same! Waste every last one of them!}
{7206}{}{Trust no one! See a number on someone's back, see a punk-replicant, kill him! Or in a minute you'll be dead yourself!}
{7207}{}{Forward! As long as we're together, we are strong!}
{7208}{}{Well said. The punks have had it coming.}
{7208}{}{Damn punks.}
{7208}{}{They have no right to live.}
{7208}{}{REVENGE! REVENGE! REVENGE!}
{7208}{}{Right on the mark!}
{7208}{}{Yes! We must kill them the moment we see them!}
{7209}{}{Die, you cursed punk!}
{7209}{}{Take that, punk?}
{7209}{}{HA! Down he goes! One less punk!}
{7209}{}{Ooooh, you replicant filth. We'll remember you. Just dare to show up here again.}
{7209}{}{Die! Die! Die! The punks must suffer!}
{7210}{}{Whoa. Punks in the city. ALARM!!!}
{7210}{}{Waste the replicant scum!}
{7210}{}{The punks are charging! Attack!}
{7210}{}{I see a punk. Everyone over here.}

# npc_dialog.fos. Строки для диалогов
# Диалог хономера и охранника. q_hub_lab.fos
{8000}{}{Who are you?}
{8001}{}{Programmer, at the request of AHS-7, to restore the functioning of the authorization system.}
{8002}{}{Brother Honomer? Excellent, you've long been awaited. You may pass. And who's this with you?}
{8003}{}{My escort. [Turns to you] AHS-7, your task is done. You're dismissed.}
# Диалог двух лаборантов
{8010}{}{Ugh...}
{8011}{}{Say, do you know who the visitors are today? }
{8012}{}{Some programmer, came to fix the authorization system...}
{8013}{}{What do we need an outside programmer for? And where's our slacker?}
{8014}{}{Ours was shot...}
{8015}{}{Whoa! What for?}
{8016}{}{A commission came to see the chief, headed by AHS-7. The boss took the commission around the lab. }
{8017}{}{They're walking, the boss explaining this and that, introducing the inspector to the staff, who's asking questions. And then they walk into the server room.}
{8018}{}{And so?}
{8019}{}{Well, that's it. They walk in, our admin, dead drunk, asleep on the server, Solitaire on the monitor, music playing... A total mess. When the boss saw it, he turned green with rage.}
{8020}{}{Damn...}
{8021}{}{Yep. The commission tore the boss a new one, drove off, and he called those guys from the surface. They put the admin against the wall and gave him a burst. How he screamed...}
{8022}{}{And what now?}
{8023}{}{Well, once he replicates, he'll come back. The boss doesn't want to fire him, you can't find another like him. For now he's called a coder from Frisco to fix a few things. The authorization system died.}
{8024}{}{So that's it... And how do you get on the network now without authorization?}
{8025}{}{Plain, no password. Right now you don't even need a login - the system's down. }
{8026}{}{Dangerous.}
{8027}{}{Well, yeah. But this guy seems to know his stuff. We'll see.}
{8028}{}{Yep...}
# HРемонт
{8029}{}{I don't understand, what is this even supposed to mean?}
{8029}{}{Comments are for the weak, sure.}
{8029}{}{Naming variables properly is just impossible, right.}
{8029}{}{To hell with Hungarian notation...}
{8029}{}{The author read a few books, but thinking with his own head, no?}
{8029}{}{Who's going to clear the buffer for you, Uncle Fyodor?}
{8029}{}{Idiot, he could've crammed in even more try-catches...}
{8029}{}{Let's read the comments... "TODO: Fix this." Fix what, dammit?}
{8029}{}{What's this... "define true equals false". And the comment... "Happy debugging, bitch". Ugh, hell.}
{8029}{}{Where do we get so many hack coders among us?}
{8029}{}{Well damn, will it even work this way? Let's see... DAMMIT! Didn't work...}
{8029}{}{Oh great, this is a month's worth of work for me...}
{8029}{}{No, really, to screw up like this. That's a talent.}
{8029}{}{The compiler won't start without a prayer... Our Father, I'll pull you by the ear! Didn't help. With a prayer it didn't start either.}
{8029}{}{An original approach... For an idiot. The garbage collector was written by the same kind of idiot, 100%.}
{8029}{}{2 + 2 = -6.5?! What the...}
{8029}{}{I'd like to find the author and ask what all this means, and why he's such a moron.}
{8029}{}{I can't understand how such a ham-fisted clod made it all the way to AHS-4. }
{8029}{}{He shouldn't be coding, he should be a clown... }
{8029}{}{Oh, what did I do to deserve all this?}
{8029}{}{What language is this anyway? Imperative Haskell? How is that even possible?!}
